      "heading": "List Partition",
      "tag": "Category",
      "bullets": [
        "Partition by discrete values",
        "Best for: region, status, tenant",
        "Each value maps to one partition",
        "Good for multi-tenant isolation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "Hash Partition",
      "tag": "Even Split",
      "bullets": [
        "Partition by hash of key",
        "Even distribution across N parts",
        "No natural range pruning",
        "Best for: random-access workloads"
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "Sharding (Citus/FDW)",
      "tag": "Scale-Out",
      "bullets": [
        "Data across multiple servers",
        "Horizontal scale beyond single node",
        "Cross-shard queries are expensive",
        "Best for: multi-TB, multi-region"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "footer": "Start with native partitioning. Shard only when single-node capacity is exceeded.",
